{
  "text": "While previous high-resolution structural studies have revealed the architectures of the late nucleolar and export-competent pre-60S particles, the architecture of the early nucleolar particles, containing specific factors such as Nsa1, remains unknown [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Although the identities and approximate binding regions of many early nucleolar ribosome assembly factors are known, their structures and functions have not yet been determined [CITATION_3] .",
